==Old English==
===Etymology===
Common Germanic *''[[lais-]]''
===Verb===
'''leornian'''

# to [[learn]], to [[teach]] 
# closely related to the word [[lore]]

===History===

Because of ''leornian's'' double meaning there has not always been a distinction between ''learn'' and ''teach''. It is a fairly recent distinction. As recently as the 18th century it was acceptable grammer to say ''The teacher learned the students their lessons.'' Then for no understood reason ''learn'' in the sense of ''teach'' discontinued in all but the south of the Unite States, where it is still in use today.
